<!--
This is the source code, it's not too special. If you came here wondering why I
end my stories with a ìèà character, you're in luck.

It's the unicode character for the Egyptian hieroglyph for a milk jug (W20 jrtjt).
You may have noticed that the favicon for my website is also a milk jug, albeit a
more modern one. Basically what it comes down to is that my last name, Leite, is
Portuguese for milk.

If your browser can't render a ìèà, get a better one. Or a better computer. Or
update your fonts. Or just deal with it. I think those are the only options.


Banner image is edited from a photograph by Stephen W. Oachs http://www.stephenoachs.com/
-->

<html>
<head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <meta lang="en-us">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width">

    <title>Writing</title>

    <link rel="icon" type="image/png" href="/writing/graphics/favicon.png">

    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Montserrat" rel="stylesheet">

    <link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="/writing/css/normalize.css">

    <link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="/writing/css/style.css">
    <link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="/writing/css/articles.css">

    <link rel="stylesheet" href="http://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/highlight.js/9.12.0/styles/default.min.css">
    <script src="http://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/highlight.js/9.12.0/highlight.min.js"></script>
    <script>
      hljs.initHighlightingOnLoad();

      /* Usually anchors scroll you such that the top of the window lines up with
          the top of the element you're scrolling to. I'd prefer a bit more space
          at the top, so I have this listener
       */
      window.addEventListener(
        "hashchange",
        () => {
          window.scrollTo(window.scrollX, window.scrollY - 100);
        }
      );
    </script>
</head>
<body>
  <img class="banner" src="/writing/graphics/sf_skyline.png">
  <div class="page">
    <div class="">
      <p class="return"><a href="/home">&lt; Back</a></p>

        <h2>Contents</h2>
        <ul class="contents">
          <% for (let i = 0; i < stories.length; i++) { %>
            <li category="creative"><a href="#<%- stories[i].slugTitle %>"><%- stories[i].title %></a></li>
          <% } %>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <hr>

      <% for (let i = 0; i < stories.length; i++) { %>
        <div class="titleWrapper" category="creative">
          <a class="imgLink" href="#<%- stories[i].slugTitle %>"><img class="link" src="/writing/graphics/icons/link.png"></a>
          <p class="title" id="<%- stories[i].slugTitle %>"><%- stories[i].title %></p>
          <a href="/writing" class="linkBack">top&nbsp;^</a>
        </div>

        <div class="article">
          <% for (let j = 0; j < stories[i].content.length; j++) { %>
            <p>
              <%- stories[i].content[j] %>
            </p>
          <% } %>
          <p class="storyEnd">ìèà</p>
        </div>
      <% } %>
    </div>
  </div>
</body>
</html>
